WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:02.961 --> 00:00:05.047
Uhh. I'm so nervous!

2
00:00:05.130 --> 00:00:06.900
It's been so long. no one
even makes fun of me

3
00:00:06.924 --> 00:00:08.383
for being unemployed anymore.

4
00:00:08.467 --> 00:00:10.844
Aw. We can make fun of you
if you want. sweetie.

5
00:00:10.969 --> 00:00:12.930
You could also
take one of these.

6
00:00:12.971 --> 00:00:14.473
It's a worry worm.

7
00:00:14.598 --> 00:00:16.618
It eats your worries
and dies out in a couple hours.

8
00:00:16.642 --> 00:00:19.061
I'm on one right now.
Super chill.

9
00:00:19.144 --> 00:00:20.771
I'm not taking breakfast drugs!

10
00:00:20.812 --> 00:00:22.105
We doing breakfast drugs?

11
00:00:22.189 --> 00:00:23.815
I'm just dropping
Morty off. Deal me in.

12
00:00:23.941 --> 00:00:25.442
Nobody's dealer-ing anyone.

13
00:00:25.526 --> 00:00:28.153
Seriously. guys. this
interview is important to me!

14
00:00:28.278 --> 00:00:29.655
Wow! Good luck. Dad!

15
00:00:29.780 --> 00:00:31.740
Didn't... Didn't realize
you were still trying.

16
00:00:31.823 --> 00:00:33.200
Yeah. Why?

17
00:00:33.325 --> 00:00:34.802
No one's on your ass
to contribute a thing.

18
00:00:34.826 --> 00:00:36.137
Ah. if you're trying to
neg me into taking a worm.

19
00:00:36.161 --> 00:00:37.287
you've succeeded.

20
00:00:37.371 --> 00:00:40.040
Negging works.

21
00:00:40.165 --> 00:00:42.042
See you all in a week! Mnh.

22
00:00:42.167 --> 00:00:43.835
I'm so excited!

23
00:00:43.961 --> 00:00:46.129
Guh-uh. this is what it feels
like to have friends?

24
00:00:46.213 --> 00:00:48.590
Wouldn't know.
Pick you up on Sunday?

25
00:00:48.674 --> 00:00:50.175
See you then!

26
00:00:51.468 --> 00:00:53.762
-Snowball!
-Morty!

27
00:00:55.180 --> 00:00:57.266
Oh. my God!
I missed you so much!

28
00:00:57.349 --> 00:00:59.476
Me too. Morty. Me too.

29
00:01:01.000 --> 00:01:07.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

30
00:01:34.386 --> 00:01:36.221
I... was there
when that happened.

31
00:01:36.346 --> 00:01:38.098
Really cool!

32
00:01:38.223 --> 00:01:40.517
Whoa! They got a monorail. too?!

33
00:01:40.559 --> 00:01:42.853
Proud of my dog.
He built this place. you know.

34
00:01:42.894 --> 00:01:44.062
UGG! Glugg UGG!

35
00:01:44.187 --> 00:01:45.354
Agh! Shit! What the fuck?

36
00:01:45.439 --> 00:01:47.482
Paul! Come! Up!
Don't mess with him.

37
00:01:47.566 --> 00:01:49.359
We don't know
if he's had his shots.

38
00:01:49.401 --> 00:01:53.030
Morty.
Oh. I see you've met a mup.

39
00:01:53.071 --> 00:01:54.531
No big deal.

40
00:01:54.573 --> 00:01:57.283
Just humanoid creatures
we bred to be pets.

41
00:01:57.366 --> 00:02:00.495
Hopefully that doesn't. heh.
freak you out too much.

42
00:02:00.579 --> 00:02:02.706
Oh. Nope.
I've seen a lot of stuff.

43
00:02:02.789 --> 00:02:05.167
Good. because it would be weird

44
00:02:05.250 --> 00:02:07.085
if you were offended by it. heh.

45
00:02:07.210 --> 00:02:08.336
since you had pets first.

46
00:02:10.088 --> 00:02:13.091
Ugh! Is there anything else
we could visit or talk about?

47
00:02:13.216 --> 00:02:15.260
Yes. Good. Good. Of course.

48
00:02:15.385 --> 00:02:17.512
BooBoo. push
the Sniff Conference.

49
00:02:17.596 --> 00:02:20.724
I've got a lot to show
my old friend.

50
00:02:20.766 --> 00:02:23.477
That's the college
of New Dog City.

51
00:02:23.602 --> 00:02:26.521
And there is our
mech-suit warehouse.

52
00:02:26.605 --> 00:02:29.066
We've updated
your grandpa's designs.

53
00:02:29.107 --> 00:02:30.567
Cool!

54
00:02:30.651 --> 00:02:33.570
I know you're probably
distracted by the mups.

55
00:02:33.654 --> 00:02:36.281
Sadly. they're all
I can see now.

56
00:02:37.074 --> 00:02:39.910
Okay. m-maybe we should
just chill at your place.

57
00:02:39.993 --> 00:02:42.788
You know? Ch-Chill? Hang?

58
00:02:49.336 --> 00:02:50.420
Water bowl. sir?

59
00:02:50.504 --> 00:02:52.297
It is our finest hose water.

60
00:02:52.422 --> 00:02:54.299
Ohh! It's shaped
like a little dog bowl.

61
00:02:54.424 --> 00:02:55.966
Tha... Hey.
That's... That's fun.

62
00:02:56.093 --> 00:02:57.594
Yes. this is good.

63
00:02:57.636 --> 00:03:01.181
We will hang by the pool
and reminisce about old times.

64
00:03:01.306 --> 00:03:02.599
No politics.

65
00:03:02.683 --> 00:03:04.118
We got company!

66
00:03:04.142 --> 00:03:05.142
God damn it!

67
00:03:05.185 --> 00:03:06.687
-Haaaa!
-Take. take!

68
00:03:06.812 --> 00:03:07.854
Jesus Christ!

69
00:03:07.979 --> 00:03:09.419
-Take. take. take!
-Take. take. take!

70
00:03:11.274 --> 00:03:13.652
You said we could keep them out!

71
00:03:13.777 --> 00:03:14.653
We're trying. sir!

72
00:03:14.778 --> 00:03:16.613
The Mancors. they're adapting!

73
00:03:16.697 --> 00:03:20.117
So we adapt harder. General.

74
00:03:20.200 --> 00:03:22.911
You're making my friend
uncomfortable.

75
00:03:22.994 --> 00:03:24.538
Okay. Morty...

76
00:03:24.663 --> 00:03:26.307
I think you're getting
the wrong impression.

77
00:03:26.331 --> 00:03:28.166
You're seeing a lot
of physical deformity

78
00:03:28.291 --> 00:03:29.710
and selective breeding.

79
00:03:29.835 --> 00:03:32.129
and your mind is going
to all kinds of places.

80
00:03:32.170 --> 00:03:34.840
I mean. it's more that this
wasn't quite the vacation I...

81
00:03:34.965 --> 00:03:37.634
Titus. take Morty
to the mup facility. mm?

82
00:03:37.676 --> 00:03:39.970
Show him how loved they are.

83
00:03:40.011 --> 00:03:41.304
Hey. buddy!

84
00:03:41.346 --> 00:03:43.305
Okay. Y-You don't
have to crouch.

85
00:03:43.348 --> 00:03:46.101
Wow. and it says here
under Other Experience:

86
00:03:46.184 --> 00:03:47.811
"jumped dimensions."

87
00:03:47.853 --> 00:03:49.187
What was that like?

88
00:03:49.312 --> 00:03:50.981
Well. you see some things. Bob.

89
00:03:51.064 --> 00:03:52.482
but at the end of the day.

90
00:03:52.566 --> 00:03:55.235
you realize we're all
pretty much the same.

91
00:03:56.987 --> 00:03:59.740
That's the kind of experience
I want to bring to the team.

92
00:03:59.865 --> 00:04:01.074
Incredible.

93
00:04:01.199 --> 00:04:02.451
So can I ask?

94
00:04:02.492 --> 00:04:04.619
Any big fish you're
trying to take down?

95
00:04:04.661 --> 00:04:07.956
Well. Jerry. I don't normally
talk clients during interviews.

96
00:04:08.039 --> 00:04:12.252
but. God. I'm just loving
this laid-back attitude!

97
00:04:12.377 --> 00:04:14.171
Nipslip Vodka.

98
00:04:14.254 --> 00:04:15.797
If we can convince them
to hire us.

99
00:04:15.881 --> 00:04:17.673
we'd double our revenue.

100
00:04:17.716 --> 00:04:18.716
Ahh.

101
00:04:18.841 --> 00:04:20.302
I mean. it's right there. Bob.

102
00:04:20.385 --> 00:04:21.803
It's screaming at ya.

103
00:04:21.887 --> 00:04:24.347
What? I-I-I don't see it.

104
00:04:25.056 --> 00:04:26.975
Drink.

105
00:04:27.058 --> 00:04:29.519
Yes. Yes! I love it!

106
00:04:29.561 --> 00:04:32.606
I love it! So simple. So great!

107
00:04:32.731 --> 00:04:34.065
Mm. These things come to me.

108
00:04:34.191 --> 00:04:35.358
Hey. You free tonight?

109
00:04:35.442 --> 00:04:37.068
We're having dinner
with their CEO.

110
00:04:37.194 --> 00:04:38.737
They need to hear this. Jerry.

111
00:04:38.862 --> 00:04:42.240
and they need to hear it from
someone as confident as you.

112
00:04:42.365 --> 00:04:47.621
♪ It's Friday. Friday.
gotta get down on Friday ♪

113
00:04:50.081 --> 00:04:52.125
-Honey. I'm home.
-Jerry?

114
00:04:52.209 --> 00:04:55.337
Prospects are good. Meeting
the client for dinner.

115
00:04:55.420 --> 00:04:57.088
Oh. Uh. that's great.

116
00:04:57.214 --> 00:04:58.882
Why did you park on the lawn?

117
00:04:58.924 --> 00:05:01.092
Jesus. How many
of these did you take?

118
00:05:01.218 --> 00:05:04.221
The first worm helped. so I
took a couple more. No biggie.

119
00:05:04.262 --> 00:05:05.806
What's up? Jerry O.D. on worms?

120
00:05:05.931 --> 00:05:07.390
I told him to take one!

121
00:05:07.474 --> 00:05:09.476
Holy shit!

122
00:05:10.769 --> 00:05:12.354
Jerry. you are teeming!

123
00:05:12.437 --> 00:05:14.105
I-I guess you had enough anxiety

124
00:05:14.231 --> 00:05:15.565
to fuel a worm breeding frenzy.

125
00:05:15.607 --> 00:05:16.900
That's a bad thing. right?

126
00:05:16.983 --> 00:05:18.652
It's a new thing.
I-I gotta admit.

127
00:05:18.777 --> 00:05:20.254
I don't know much
about the worm business.

128
00:05:20.278 --> 00:05:22.155
I'm sure my worm
dealer has a fix.

129
00:05:22.280 --> 00:05:24.908
J-Man's gonna pass on all this.

130
00:05:24.991 --> 00:05:26.284
Honey. you're teeming!

131
00:05:26.409 --> 00:05:28.954
Alright. But let's
wrap this quick.

132
00:05:29.079 --> 00:05:30.789
Big night ahead.

133
00:05:30.914 --> 00:05:32.457
No more giving Jerry drugs.

134
00:05:32.582 --> 00:05:34.417
Loud and clear.

135
00:05:35.460 --> 00:05:37.212
You like that?

136
00:05:37.295 --> 00:05:39.089
We call it a mup-a-cino!

137
00:05:39.172 --> 00:05:40.966
Mmm! Creamy!

138
00:05:41.091 --> 00:05:44.302
Biscuit. this is Emperor
Snowball's "Morty."

139
00:05:44.427 --> 00:05:45.595
As you can see. Morty.

140
00:05:45.637 --> 00:05:47.764
it's all totally fine.

141
00:05:47.806 --> 00:05:49.432
I'm kind of getting
the impression

142
00:05:49.516 --> 00:05:51.393
that you're all sort of
ashamed of this stuff.

143
00:05:51.476 --> 00:05:53.228
Ashamed? He seems unconvinced.

144
00:05:53.311 --> 00:05:54.938
I'll play the video.

145
00:05:55.021 --> 00:05:57.190
And thanks
to new breakthroughs

146
00:05:57.315 --> 00:05:58.859
in cruelty-free Mup technology.

147
00:05:58.984 --> 00:06:01.278
you can further customize
your new best friend

148
00:06:01.361 --> 00:06:03.947
with our drag-and-drop display.

149
00:06:05.323 --> 00:06:06.783
Hahaha! And the mups like it!

150
00:06:06.867 --> 00:06:09.452
Non-genetic modifications
can also be made

151
00:06:09.494 --> 00:06:11.121
once your mup is born.

152
00:06:11.162 --> 00:06:12.664
and once the stitch is healed.

153
00:06:12.789 --> 00:06:15.876
your new friend is ready
to join the family.

154
00:06:16.001 --> 00:06:17.377
Super normal!

155
00:06:17.502 --> 00:06:19.963
And if you think it's weird.
you're weird.

156
00:06:23.675 --> 00:06:25.427
Brought you a friiiend!

157
00:06:26.678 --> 00:06:28.555
That's a happy wheeze!

158
00:06:28.680 --> 00:06:31.308
Aww. He thinks
they're inside the TV.

159
00:06:31.349 --> 00:06:33.476
Play him the video again!

160
00:06:33.560 --> 00:06:35.687
Morty? Oh. Hey... Hey. pal.

161
00:06:35.812 --> 00:06:37.188
Glad I caught you. actually.

162
00:06:37.314 --> 00:06:38.648
I-I'm just gonna take off.

163
00:06:38.690 --> 00:06:40.692
Got some homework
I forgot about. Uh...

164
00:06:40.817 --> 00:06:43.236
-Great seeing you. though.
-Right.

165
00:06:43.361 --> 00:06:44.946
So you're going to cancel me?

166
00:06:45.030 --> 00:06:46.031
What? No.

167
00:06:46.156 --> 00:06:47.657
So you're not gonna run

168
00:06:47.699 --> 00:06:49.176
and tell your grandfather
I'm doing eugenics?

169
00:06:49.200 --> 00:06:51.578
You're projecting so much
specific shit onto me!

170
00:06:51.703 --> 00:06:52.954
You think I'm racist.

171
00:06:53.038 --> 00:06:55.665
Listen. I came here
as your friend.

172
00:06:55.707 --> 00:06:57.667
That's how I wanna leave.

173
00:06:57.751 --> 00:07:00.462
Okay. Just had a lot planned.

174
00:07:00.545 --> 00:07:02.881
Didn't even get to see
our giant sprinkler.

175
00:07:03.006 --> 00:07:04.966
Next time. O-Okay?

176
00:07:05.050 --> 00:07:06.551
Okay...

177
00:07:15.226 --> 00:07:17.371
Please don't try to kill me.
Please don't try to kill me.

178
00:07:17.395 --> 00:07:18.563
Please don't try to kill me.

179
00:07:18.688 --> 00:07:20.273
Oh. shit!

180
00:07:20.398 --> 00:07:21.942
God damn it!

181
00:07:22.067 --> 00:07:24.486
-Oh. God!
-On the ground! Down! Down!

182
00:07:29.199 --> 00:07:31.868
Get out of the road.
you dumb mup!

183
00:07:31.952 --> 00:07:33.495
Oh... no...

184
00:07:39.584 --> 00:07:40.961
Oh. fuck me!

185
00:07:41.086 --> 00:07:42.730
-Take. take. take. take!
-Take. take. take. take!

186
00:07:42.754 --> 00:07:45.715
Wait! Maybe they can't
see us if we don't move!

187
00:07:45.757 --> 00:07:48.635
Never mind! Run!

188
00:07:48.760 --> 00:07:51.304
Take-take?

189
00:07:51.429 --> 00:07:55.141
Ugh. Please don't take me
to join some kind of rebellion.

190
00:07:55.266 --> 00:07:57.894
Yah. Take-take.

191
00:07:57.936 --> 00:08:00.814
Aww. man!

192
00:08:04.776 --> 00:08:07.112
Uh. hello? Sweet Marie?

193
00:08:09.906 --> 00:08:11.574
Brought the whole family. huh?

194
00:08:11.616 --> 00:08:12.742
We're cool.

195
00:08:12.784 --> 00:08:15.620
Yeah. we're... ice cold.

196
00:08:16.955 --> 00:08:19.040
As you can see.
my idiot kinda-husband

197
00:08:19.124 --> 00:08:20.667
took too many Flaxar worms.

198
00:08:20.750 --> 00:08:22.419
and they are now
reproducing inside him.

199
00:08:22.460 --> 00:08:24.754
Cha-ching! You want to go 60/40?

200
00:08:24.796 --> 00:08:26.941
We're trying to fix him. not
get into the worm business.

201
00:08:26.965 --> 00:08:28.800
Well. hold on.
Who's getting that 60?

202
00:08:28.925 --> 00:08:31.803
Dad. we are not letting this
woman harvest Jerry for worms!

203
00:08:31.928 --> 00:08:35.472
Marie? You texted "Come in"
and then a gun emoji?

204
00:08:36.474 --> 00:08:37.600
Yah!

205
00:08:41.938 --> 00:08:44.774
God damn it. Dad! Good
dealers don't grow on trees!

206
00:08:44.858 --> 00:08:46.109
Infinite multiverse. sweetie.

207
00:08:46.192 --> 00:08:48.069
There are trees that do that.

208
00:08:56.161 --> 00:08:57.620
Shit. Jerry!

209
00:08:57.704 --> 00:08:59.289
Hmm. We better find him fast.

210
00:08:59.330 --> 00:09:01.458
If the worms hit a tipping
point on Jerry's anxiety.

211
00:09:01.541 --> 00:09:03.960
they'll start using him to
feed on other people's worry.

212
00:09:04.044 --> 00:09:06.713
You mean... He's going to
feed on creating discomfort.

213
00:09:06.838 --> 00:09:09.174
Oh. boy. He'll be great at it.

214
00:09:10.508 --> 00:09:11.788
Jerry's tracker
disappeared here.

215
00:09:11.843 --> 00:09:13.303
The worms must have eaten it.

216
00:09:13.344 --> 00:09:14.989
Those things impress me
more and more by the minute.

217
00:09:15.013 --> 00:09:17.348
They're a gold mine.
Hold on.

218
00:09:18.850 --> 00:09:20.602
Surprise improv on the subway!

219
00:09:20.685 --> 00:09:22.395
Hey. want to jump in. sir?

220
00:09:22.520 --> 00:09:24.290
We could
play aging rock stars. luv.

221
00:09:24.314 --> 00:09:26.316
Shall we get cream-
crackered-knackered?

222
00:09:26.399 --> 00:09:28.610
Taking him to that improv
class was a mistake.

223
00:09:28.651 --> 00:09:30.779
Why wouldn't that be
worry-worm heaven?

224
00:09:30.862 --> 00:09:32.322
'Cause Jerry loves it.

225
00:09:32.405 --> 00:09:34.175
Uh. no. these things
must be trying to max out.

226
00:09:34.199 --> 00:09:35.992
Jerry's anxiety specifically.

227
00:09:36.034 --> 00:09:37.660
Where could he go to create

228
00:09:37.702 --> 00:09:39.913
the most discomfort
for everyone involved?

229
00:09:40.038 --> 00:09:41.838
-His client dinner!
-Client dinner?

230
00:09:41.873 --> 00:09:44.292
Right. Why he did the worms
in the first place.

231
00:09:44.375 --> 00:09:45.919
Do I have Long COVID?

232
00:09:46.044 --> 00:09:47.796
-Take. take. take!
-Take. take. take!

233
00:09:47.879 --> 00:09:50.340
-Take. take. take!
-Take. take. take!

234
00:09:53.343 --> 00:09:56.096
-Take. take. take!
-Take. take. take!

235
00:09:56.221 --> 00:09:58.556
Oh. Cool. Y-You have
a leader already.

236
00:09:58.681 --> 00:09:59.961
Y-You don't... You don't need me

237
00:10:00.016 --> 00:10:01.726
as your Dances for Wolves.

238
00:10:01.851 --> 00:10:03.853
With Wolves? I haven't seen it.

239
00:10:03.937 --> 00:10:06.022
Ha! That's sidelines talk.

240
00:10:06.106 --> 00:10:09.359
You clearly don't understand
what we're up against.

241
00:10:09.400 --> 00:10:12.320
The dogs have a breeding
program in the city.

242
00:10:12.403 --> 00:10:14.197
They raised us in cages!

243
00:10:14.239 --> 00:10:16.491
Our bodies were
twisted then ripped

244
00:10:16.574 --> 00:10:17.854
from our mothers!

245
00:10:17.909 --> 00:10:19.327
I-I probably know some of this.

246
00:10:19.369 --> 00:10:22.247
They made me watch the
mup video. Three times.

247
00:10:22.372 --> 00:10:24.624
"Mup" is the language
of the oppressor!

248
00:10:24.749 --> 00:10:27.168
You're still trapped
in their way of thinking!

249
00:10:27.210 --> 00:10:28.920
Again. just getting out
in front of this.

250
00:10:29.045 --> 00:10:30.672
I'm not looking to get caught up

251
00:10:30.755 --> 00:10:33.299
in all the colonization.
eugenics. hierarchies.

252
00:10:33.424 --> 00:10:34.968
Above my pay grade.

253
00:10:35.051 --> 00:10:37.171
Humans kind of started this
cycle a billion years ago.

254
00:10:37.220 --> 00:10:38.680
You don't want me involved.

